2 HOUSE BILL 1359
1 (I) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION DOES NOT
2 RENEW A CONTRACT FOR STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES FOR CAUSE,
3 AND AT THE END OF THE CONTRACT TERM, CONTRACTS WITH ANOTHER PRIVATE
4 PERSON TO PROVIDE THE SERVICES; OR
5 (II) THE PERSON THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING THE STUDENT
6 BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES:
7 1. HAS BEEN FOUND TO HAVE ACTED IN A MANNER
8 THREATENING TO PUBLIC HEALTH OR SAFETY;
9 2. HAS BEEN FOUND TO HAVE COMMITTED A MATERIAL
10 BREACH OF A CONTRACT FOR STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES; OR
11 3. REFUSES TO CONTINUE TO PROVIDE STUDENT BUS
12 TRANSPORTATION SERVICES UNDER THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF AN EXISTING
13 AGREEMENT.
14 (B) AT LEAST 10 YEARS BEFORE TAKING ANY ACTION THAT RESULTS IN THE
15 DISPLACEMENT OF A PERSON THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING STUDENT BUS
16 TRANSPORTATION SERVICES IN CHARLES COUNTY, THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD
17 OF EDUCATION SHALL:
18 (1) PROVIDE WRITTEN NOTICE OF THE INTENT TO DISPLACE, SENT BY
19 FIRST–CLASS MAIL AT LEAST 45 DAYS BEFORE THE HEARING REQUIRED UNDER
20 ITEM (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, TO EACH PERSON THAT PROVIDES THE SERVICES IN
21 CHARLES COUNTY; AND
22 (2) (I) HOLD AT LEAST ONE PUBLIC HEARING ON THE
23 ADVISABILITY OF THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION PROVIDING THE
24 STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES; AND
25 (II) PROVIDE NOTICE OF THE HEARING TO THE PUBLIC BY
26 PUBLISHING A NOTIFICATION IN A NEWSPAPER OF GENERAL CIRCULATION IN THE
27 COUNTY ONCE EACH WEEK FOR 2 SUCCESSIVE WEEKS BEFORE THE HEARING.
28 (C) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, WITHIN 1
29 YEAR AFTER THE PUBLIC HEARING, AND AT LEAST 5 YEARS BEFORE ANY
30 DISPLACEMENT, THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION SHALL PROVIDE
31 WRITTEN NOTICE BY REGISTERED MAIL OF THE DISPLACEMENT TO THE PERSON
32 PROVIDING THE STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES.

HOUSE BILL 1359 3
1 (2) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION MAY BEGIN
2 PROVIDING STUDENT BUS TRANSPORTATION SERVICES OR CONTRACT WITH
3 ANOTHER PERSON TO PROVIDE THE SERVICES LESS THAN 5 YEARS AFTER
4 PROVIDING THE NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION IF:
5 (I) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION PAYS THE
6 DISPLACED PERSON THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING THE SERVICES AN AMOUNT EQUAL
7 TO THE PERSON’S GROSS RECEIPTS FOR PROVIDING THE SERVICES IN THE COUNTY
8 FOR THE PRECEDING 24–MONTH PERIOD;
9 (II) THE CHARLES COUNTY BOARD OF EDUCATION AND THE
10 PERSON THAT HAS BEEN PROVIDING THE SERVICES AGREE TO A DIFFERENT NOTICE
11 PERIOD OR COMPENSATION AMOUNT; OR
12 (III) THE PERSON STOPS PROVIDING THE SERVICES IN THE
13 COUNTY.
14 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
15 1, 2025.

